<br>
It's pretty moot anyways.<br>
<br>
1. Some servers still haven't killed Ventani. Getting up to the point of killing him is a very long process of properly equipping members, steps that *can't* be skipped. You try to farm ToV armor before the majority in the guild have plane or kunark armor, you're just going to get pulverized. Of the five first brood dragons only Klandicar is a pushover and even he is far beyond the server's abilities for at least two more months. Then you have to farm him, Sontalak, Zlandicar, and if it gets that far, Lendiniara and Yelinak to get enough people with keys to Sleeper's Tomb. To do that you need ToV equipment and epics because none of them can ever be called gimmies (maybe Zlandicar). ToV and especially epics mean having to keep your guild happy when it's just human nature for people to disagree over loot decisions and get tired of doing something very dangerous for one or two people's benefit. Couple that occasional disgruntlement with guilds splitting and reshaping. Then you have to get your melees using primal, and though it might make many of you boggle believe it or not Sleepers raids are probably THE most BORING thing in EQ. That's more time gone. Then finally you have to do it despite your own guildmembers being reluctant to do it since once freed the warders don't spawn, no more SoDs etc etc. And then you actually have to DO it, Ventani, while not insanely hard, is not exactly easy either; bringing 30 people isn't going to cut it.<br>
<br>
2. FV's population is very VERY low and EQ is on its downturn now, there aren't enough people replacing those who leave. And this is not likely to change; its actually much more likely to increase.<br>
<br>
3. This server has the unique problem of having to separate good and evil. This guarantees two (at least) fairly equal 'uberguilds' (I know they don't like being called that) which cannot cooperate with each other in this sort of thing even if they want to (no guarantees).<br>
<br>
Unless something very profound happens in EQ this year, like another expansion with more than cosmetic changes, this server will never get to the very end of things like freeing Kerafyrm is. Or even Vulak. Or whatever the new steamrollers in Sshra and the other new luclin zones are. It's not a comment on FnF's skills or any other guild's, its simply a comment on the server's resources *never* being up to the task. Not before everyone is tired of EQ, at least.<br>
